comment_regular_data.body:
@anihm136 

I'm also very close to full v-block mode support - hopefully only multi-width backwards v-block edge cases to iron out. Once finished, I'll commit it to telescope for review to ultimately make a PR to refactor `vim.region` with full char, line, and block-selection support. (telescope commit will ease review and debugging as it returns visual selection rather than region)

In addition, `vim.get_visual_selection` probably should feature arguments `trim` (default=true) and `delimiter` (default=' ' ?) such that users can optionally augment their output. I'm also afraid visual block mode support will require significant changes to how positions of marks are retrieved (will be factored out) as more info from `vim.fn.getpos` is needed than presented here to later resolve visual columns (as in, actual screen columns).
